<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-726] Add ReplicaFetcherThread name to mbean names</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-726</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;1. Add ReplicaFetcherThread name to mbean names via clientId.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2. Use a uniform format for thread names in ConsumerFetcherThread and ReplicaFetcherThread.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;3. Modify the way kafka.server.FetcherStats are created so that the thread name is not appended twice to the mbean name.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
